{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "24", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "04", "M": "07", "S": "05"}}, "news": [{"title": "Uttar Pradesh's state cabinet approves ordinance simplifying land-use conversion", "para": "Uttar Pradesh cabinet approved an ordinance simplifying land-use conversion, integrating it with building plan approvals to boost industrial growth. A policy to treat and reuse wastewater was also cleared, aiming to conserve drinking water resources. Additionally, funds were allocated for a 7km road for the Sambhal 24 Kosi Parikrama, easing devotee access.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/uttar-pradesh-cabinet-approves-land-use-conversion-ordinance-to-streamline-development-processes/129765519?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-37750/129765519.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "BMC asks MMRDA & MHADA to settle \u20b92,287 crore property tax dues", "para": "The Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation (BMC) has demanded over Rs 2,287 crore in property tax from the Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority (MMRDA) and Maharashtra Housing and Area Development Authority (Mhada). These dues are critical for funding civic services and infrastructure projects across Mumbai. The BMC is actively pursuing recovery to strengthen its financial position.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/bmc-demands-2287-crore-in-property-tax-from-mmrda-and-mhada/129765487?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-80216/129765487.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Uttar Pradesh clears private business park policy to woo global firms", "para": "Uttar Pradesh's cabinet has approved the Private Business Park Development Scheme-2025, aiming to attract global companies and R&D centers with world-class plug-and-play infrastructure. This policy will expedite project setup, boost investment, and generate thousands of jobs, particularly in the services and technology sectors. Developed under a DBFOT model, these parks will feature a 45-year concession period for private developers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/uttar-pradesh-unveils-ambitious-private-business-park-initiative-to-attract-global-investment/129765467?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-29888/129765467.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}]}